<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 23 at 6:20PM CDT  by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Hamilton,
northwestern Coryell and southwestern Bosque Counties through 645 PM
CDT...
At 619 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Hamilton, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Evant and Cranfills Gap.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
